  "body": "https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes/pull/8628 introduced breaking behavior to `kubectl delete all --all`\n\nIt isn't good to require users to specify `--ignore-not-found` in the normal case of deleting all replication controllers (which cascade to pods), then getting NotFound errors on previously resolved pods. Anyone who had previously scripted `kubectl delete all --all` will now get a failure.\n\nI think `--ignore-not-found` should default to true when used with `--all`. Since the user is not specifying a particular resource name, they just want everything found removed, I think ignoring NotFound errors captures the intent.\n\n@jlowdermilk \n",
